article.headline: Wyoming 100, Western St., Colo. 73
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- Sean Ogirri scored 26 points and Brandon Ewing added 21 to help Wyoming to a 100-73 win over Western State on Tuesday night. Afam Muojeke had 18 points and Tyson Johnson finished with 10 for the Cowboys (8-1). Wyoming led 44-35 at the break, and extended its lead in the second half as Ogirri went 6-of-9 from 3-point range. The Cowboys took a 20-point lead midway through the second half. Brandon Gentry led the Mountaineers (5-4) with 17 points. Cameron Burney and Allen McFarland added 16 points apiece.
